Cody wiped his brow. The passage led him straight forward, with no corners or slopes to block vision. This advantage that was lost on the human, as he squinted into the darkness. “And nothing to hide behind, either,” he muttered. He took in the faint scratch of Lulu's paws on the floor, and amended his statement. “Nothing for me to hide behind, anyway. You get to hide behind me, don't you?” Glancing behind, he was a little startled that Lulu was nowhere in sight.
